                    <span>I have had a hard time in the past listening to Debbie Ford because her voice is a little boring, but this time I just pictured her as my girlfriend on Prozac sitting across the table from me and we got along great. After just a few minutes you pick up on her genuineness and feel her emotions as she relates her personal story.  She hit upon insights to the past and how the bad things have gone on to create good things in our present self.  I nearly fell over with a revelation about me, after one of her meditations.  I have since purchased this set for three  friends and each one has said the same thing, it is lifechanging. 
<br />You can start to collect your fragments and bring them back and love them.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Don't buy if you don't want major change in your life</div>
